netfirewall (0.5.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Self-contained .NET publish — the runtime travels inside the package; drop
    the dotnet-runtime / aspnetcore-runtime dependencies and the Microsoft APT
    repository requirement. Adds libicu to Depends (culture-aware app).
  * Ship the DHCP server and the deployment doctor binaries.
  * Split provisioning into a secret-free postinst (users, dirs, units, env
    TEMPLATES verbatim) and a per-appliance netfirewall-firstboot.service that
    generates the master key + DB password, inits the local cluster, creates the
    role/DB, runs migrations + seeds, and starts the services. Prevents flashed
    appliance images from sharing one TOTP master key / DB password.
  * Install the bootstrap wrapper (/usr/local/bin/netfirewall-bootstrap) and
    enable netfirewall-bootstrap.service so the firewall reconciles DB→kernel
    each boot.
  * postrm purge mirrors uninstall.sh --purge and drops the LOCAL DB/role only.

 -- NetFirewall Project <noreply@example.invalid>  Sat, 06 Jun 2026 23:30:00 +0000

netfirewall (0.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging.
  * Bundles daemon, web, TUI, migrations, and the WAN monitor binaries.
  * Wraps deploy/install.sh logic into debhelper postinst / prerm scripts.
  * Configures Daemon__AcceptedPeerUids with the netfirewall-web UID + root
    so `sudo netfirewall-tui` reaches the socket from console.

